# Three.js Game Modules

## Scene objects

- Dispose geometries/materials when removing meshes from long-lived scenes.
- Prefer `InstancedMesh` for many identical enemies/projectiles — no per-entity Mesh in horde paths.
- Reuse `Vector3` / `Object3D` instances in hot loops; avoid `new` per frame.

## Loading

- GLB via `GLTFLoader`; cache loaded assets; don't reload per spawn.
- Ground Y / `feetY` / `groundY` must stay consistent for combat and HP bars.

## Updates

- `EnemyManager.updateInstance` and `ENEMY_MESH_LIFT` must stay in sync with `getEnemyHpBarWorldY`.
- Spatial hash / despawn radius: changing `ARENA_SIZE` requires revisiting spawn and despawn constants.

## Performance

- Test at 300+ enemies when touching spawn, collision, or terrain physics.
- Shadow casters: minimize count; instancing already handles enemy draw calls.

```js
// BAD — mesh per enemy in horde
for (const e of enemies) scene.add(new THREE.Mesh(geo, mat));

// GOOD — instanced pool
enemyMesh.setMatrixAt(i, matrix);
enemyMesh.instanceMatrix.needsUpdate = true;
```
